<item>
            <title>[SEC-1344] CAS Documentation Errors</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-1344</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The CAS documentation for Spring Security is vague and contains a few errors.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;First, the &amp;lt;bean id=&quot;casAuthenticationProvider&quot;&amp;gt; element contains the tag &amp;lt;security:custom-authentication-provider /&amp;gt; which is not allowed by the spring-security-3.0.xsd.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have configured the authentication provider accordingly:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;security:authentication-manager alias=&quot;authenticationManager&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
	&amp;lt;security:authentication-provider ref=&quot;casAuthenticationProvider&quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/security:authentication-provider&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/security:authentication-manager&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Second, the &amp;lt;security:http&amp;gt; section can be more specific IMHO. I have configured it like shown below. I don`t know if this is &apos;the&apos; way to configure it, but it works.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;security:http entry-point-ref=&quot;casAuthenticationEntryPoint&quot; auto-config=&quot;true&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
	...&lt;br/&gt;
	&amp;lt;security:custom-filter position=&quot;CAS_FILTER&quot; ref=&quot;casAuthenticationFilter&quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/security:custom-filter&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/security:http&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Third, the &amp;lt;bean id=&quot;casFilter&quot; class=&quot;org.springframework.security.cas.web.CasAuthenticationFilter&quot;&amp;gt; contains the properties &amp;lt;property name=&quot;authenticationFailureUrl&quot; value=&quot;/casfailed.jsp&quot;/&amp;gt; and &amp;lt;property name=&quot;defaultTargetUrl&quot; value=&quot;/&quot;/&amp;gt; which do not exist anymore.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Once you have figured this out, it works really great &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cheers, Stephan&lt;/p&gt;





</description>
